Documentation for arch_spec_orbacus.mk

Note: arch_spec_orbacus.mk must be included before standard.mk.

User input:
    IDLFILES=<list of idl files>
            The pathnames should be listed relative to the release.
            example: IDLFILES=pkgA/idl/foo.idl pkgB/weirddir/bar.idl

User output:
    STUBCPPFILES
            contains a list of the genrerated C++ files.
    SKELCPPFILES
            contains a list of the generated C++ skeleton files.
            
Example:
    The srt repository contains the packages ProvidesIDL and UsesIDL. Together
    they form an example of how to use arch_spec_orbacus.mk.
